.Dd September 29, 2025
.Dt REVOLTE 1
.Sh NAME
.Nm revolte
.Nd ultra-small GPL Wolfenstein 3D clone
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl hwf
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is a fast shooter game in which the player navigates
through several levels to complete his mission for
saving the world from revolting robots.

The game was made in "keep it simple" spirit, aiming
to be very small, efficient and dependency-free,
which makes it very portable and moddable. As there
are many different versions of the game now, it is
possible that some will differ in some aspects from
the default SDL version assumed by this manual page.
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl h
Print help and exit.
.It Fl w
Force the game to run in window.
.It Fl f
Force the game to run in full-screen mode.
.El

.Sh CONTROLS
In its most basic form the game is playable with only 4 arrow
keys and 3 additional buttons. The SDL version further adds
mouse support and additional buttons for the user's comfort. By
default the controls are mapped as follows.

.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It movement keys ([WSADQE], or [ARROWS], or [NUMPAD]), mouse
Used to move and look around.
.It [SPACE]
Makes the player jump.
.It button 1 ([LMB], [J], [RETURN], [CTRL])
Shoot or confirm.
.It button 2 ([K], [SHIFT])
Strafe or cancel.
.It button 3 ([L])
Helper button for consoles.
.It [O], [P], [X], [Y], [Z], mouse wheel
Change weapons.
.It [F]
Cycle current and previous weapon.
.It [TAB]
Show map.
.It [ESCAPE]
Open menu.
.El

.Sh CONFIGURATION
The basic version of the game doesn't use any config files. Instead,
configuration is done by changing values in the source code
.Ar settings.h
file and recompiling the game. For more information refer to the game's
README and comments in the source code itself.
